        <abstract>
            <p>JDH has probably influenced Bates by pointing out applicability of CD’s views to his cases.</p>
            <p>Is greatly puzzled by difference in effect of external conditions on individual animals and plants. Cannot conceive that climate could affect even such a single character as a hooked seed.</p>
            <p>Does not think Huxley is right about "saltus".</p>
        </abstract>
